message.entry: ''SamplePoints'' of type datetime not supported when method is ''linear''.
''SamplePoints'' function handle must return a logical scalar.
''SamplePoints'' value must be a vector of type double, single, duration, or datetime.
The sample points vector length must be {0}, the same as the size of the input data in the operating dimension.
Window length argument must be a duration scalar or a 2-element duration vector when ''SamplePoints'' value is a datetime or duration vector.
{0} value must not contain Inf or {1}.
''SamplePoints'' of type single are not supported for duration and datetime arrays.
{0} value must be sorted in ascending order.
''SamplePoints'' parameter not supported when first argument is a timetable.
